Description: Body fragment of East Greek pottery dinos. Part of two friezes, guilloche and probably Wild Goat band, with only filling ornament and part of an animal preserved.
Producer name: Attributed to: The London Dinos Group
Curator's comments: Object owned and held by Antikenmuseum, Heidelberg. This record is included in the British Museum database as part of the Museum’s Naukratis Project, a research collaboration that aims to virtually re-unite finds from the ancient port city of Naukratis, now distributed over 80 museums worldwide.
Bibliographic references: CVA Heidelberg I / Corpus Vasorum Antiquorum Heidelberg Universität Band I (p.11, no. 26, pl. 2, no.26)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GK.77)
